Objective¶

To predict the concrete strength using the data available in file concrete_data.xls. Apply feature engineering and model tuning to obtain 80% to 95% of R2score.

Import Libraries¶

In [1164]:

InteractiveShell.ast_node_interactivity='all'

  • ash does not show any significant relation with water, superplatic, coarseagg, fineagg and age.
  • water shows negative relationship (linear) with superplastic and fineagg while does not show any significant relationship with others.
  • superplastic shows negative linear relationship with water and does not show any significant relationship with others.
  • coarseagg does not show any significant relation with any other columns.
  • fineagg has negative linear relationship with water and it does not show any significant relation with any others.

Perform Random Search¶

Perform Randomized search on Random Forest¶

In [1259]:
n_estimators = [int(x) for x in np.linspace(start = 100, stop = 1000, num = 10)]
# Number of features to consider at every split
max_features = ['auto', 'sqrt']
# Maximum number of levels in tree
max_depth = [int(x) for x in np.linspace(10, 110, num = 11)]
max_depth.append(None)
# Minimum number of samples required to split a node
min_samples_split = [2, 5, 10]
